{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/cli-reference.md#cli-commands", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/cli-reference.md", "anchor": "cli-commands", "breadcrumb": "CLI reference > CLI commands", "level": 2, "position": 1, "text": "You can start sessions, pipe content, resume conversations, and manage updates with these commands:\n\nIf you mistype a subcommand, Claude Code suggests the closest match and exits without starting a session. For example, `claude udpate` prints `Did you mean claude update?`.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": []}
